          MODULE=conspy
         VERSION=1.16
          SOURCE=$MODULE-$VERSION.tar.gz
      SOURCE_URL=$SFORGE_URL/$MODULE/$MODULE-$VERSION-1/
      SOURCE_VFY=sha256:ee5ef648ea08d20d9062db22e7bf62a7b7261af02053f916016d1b80a66a5609
        WEB_SITE=http://conspy.sourceforge.net/
         ENTERED=20201001
         UPDATED=20201001
           SHORT="Remote control of Linux virtual consoles"

cat << EOF
Conspy allows a (possibly remote) user to see what is displayed on a Linux
virtual console, and send keystrokes to it. conspy asks the Linux kernel for
the virtual console's frame buffer. That is, it gets an image of what is
displayed on the screen and makes your terminal look the same.
EOF
